_input_tnm: Disseminated cell sample collected from the bone marrow of a patient with localized prostate cancer. After enrichment for epithelial cells, EpCaM (CD326; a pan-epithelial cell antigen)positive cells were identified and isolated into pools of cells by micropipetting. The pools of 10-20 disseminated cells from each patient were amplified by ligation mediated PCR then labeled by random priming for array CGH analysis. Patient's tumor: Gleason grade 7 and TNM stage T3a.

Disseminated-cell sample detected by EpCaM positivity and isolated by micropipetting from the bone marrow of a patient with advanced prostate cancer. 10-20 disseminated cells from each patient were pooled and amplified by ligation mediated PCR then labeled by random priming for array CGH analysis. Patient was Gleason grade 7, TNM stage T4N1, was treated by radical retropubic prostatectomy (RRP), and received no hormone therapy. Bone marrow was collected just prior to RRP.

NO INFORMATION ON NODAL STATUS.  NOTE:  DONOR TREATED WITH NEOADJUVANT CHEMOTHERAPY., >90
